---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<BaseLayout title="Stefano Trentin — Curriculum — Società Filarmonica di Turriaco" lang="en" currentPage="corsi">
  <div class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="page-header-back"><a href={`${base}/en/corsi`}>← Our Courses</a></p>
      <h1>Stefano Trentin</h1>
      <p class="page-header-sub">Trumpet</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <div style="display: flex; justify-content: center; margin: 0 0 40px;">
        <img
          src={`${base}/asset/images/tondo_stefano.jpg`}
          alt="Stefano Trentin"
          style="width: 160px; height: 160px; border-radius: 50%; object-fit: cover; border: 2px solid var(--color-secondary, #8b6f47);"
        />
      </div>
      <p>He began his musical studies at age 6 at the music school of the <em>Tita Michelas</em> band in Fiumicello under the guidance of Maestro Gino Comisso, who instilled in him a passion for the trumpet. He subsequently continued his studies with Maestros Gabriele Boscarato, Federico Biondi and Loris Beltrame, always within the same music school.</p>
      <p>From 2020 to 2025 he took part in the National Youth Symphony Band promoted by ANBIMA.</p>
      <p>In 2023 he began his studies at the <em>Jacopo Tomadini</em> Conservatory in Udine under the guidance of Maestro Carlo Beltrami and at the same time participated in various advanced masterclasses at European and extra-European level, such as the <em>Italian Brass Week</em> and the <em>Music System Italy/Japan</em>, with internationally renowned teachers including: Andrea Dell'Ira, Andrea Tofanelli, Rex Richardson, Omar Tomasoni, Ottaviano Cristofoli, Francisco "Pacho" Flores, Jens Lindemann, Piergiuseppe Doldi, Marco Pierobon, Jure Gradišnik and Bertold Stecher.</p>
      <p>He collaborates with the <em>Dolomiti Symphonie</em> orchestra, the Opera Prima Wien orchestra, the <em>Fil(m)armonica</em> orchestra of Mossa and the <em>Val Isonzo</em> wind orchestra, while also carrying out regular service in the conservatory's own productions, such as the opera <em>Gianni Schicchi</em> by Giacomo Puccini performed at Mittelfest 2024.</p>
      <p>In 2024 he took part in the EYBB (<em>European Youth Brass Band</em>) promoted by EBBA (<em>European Brass Band Association</em>) at the European brass band championships held in Palanga (Lithuania), where he served as principal cornet.</p>
      <p>He teaches at several band music schools: <em>Tita Michelas</em> of Fiumicello, <em>Società Filarmonica</em> of Turriaco, <em>Gioacchino Rossini</em> of Castions di Strada, and takes part annually in the Band@scuola project, through which he teaches brass instruments to primary school children.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-header-back {
    font-size: 14px;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    opacity: 0.8;
  }
  .page-header-back a {
    color: inherit;
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .page-header-back a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
  .page-header-sub {
    font-size: 1rem;
    opacity: 0.8;
    margin-top: 4px;
    font-style: italic;
  }
</style>
